article.linkText: Quinnipiac beats Saint Peter's 84-73 for 10th straight victory
article.story: HAMDEN, Conn. -- — Amarri Tice and Rihards Vavers scored 18 points apiece and Quinnipiac beat Saint Peter's 84-73 for its 10 straight victory on Thursday night. Tice had six rebounds and Vavers grabbed five for the Bobcats (19-4, 11-1 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Paul Otieno scored 15 on 6-for-7 shooting. The Peacocks (11-10, 7-5) were led by the 17 points of Roy Clarke. Armoni Zeigler had 14 points and Latrell Reid added 12 points and four assists. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
